2.5.4_merge_branch.commit_message:
Release 2.5.4

Refer to README.txt for changes

Change the sorting order when min_max_valid

The current sorting order is picking based on the max power settings,
which has opposite affect.
For example if there is a table like this with ITM:
target:\_SB_.PC00.LPCB.ECDV.SKIN  trip_temp:46 pl1_min:45000 pl1.max:76000
target:\_SB_.PC00.LPCB.ECDV.SEN5  trip_temp:60 pl1_min:15000 pl1.max:45000

If first SKIN temperature is >= 46, then range for PL changes is from
76W to 45W.
While the above condition is active if SEN5 >= 60, the range is from
45W to 15W. So the loweest PL1 should go upto 15W.

With current sorting the lowest PL1 will be 45W, as in the sorted list
SKIN will be above SEN5. Hence, SKIN will own RAPL for controls till
skin temp < 60.

So change the order so that in this case SEN5 will be before SKIN.

Process case when target matches after init

It is possible that during init adaptive target matched. But later
some conditions changed, then remove default and install the matched
target. When the condition no longer matches install the default
one.

Merge pull request #409 from ColinIanKing/master

Minor code clean-up janitorial fixes, address issues found with static analysis tool

Remove memset for pid_param_t to 0

Use initialization of individual fields to avoid portability complians
from compilers.

Fix for issue:#408

Remove check for new_passive < critical

In cthd_engine_default::add_int340x_processor_dev(void) the value ofi
new_passive is less than critical by 15000, so the check for new_passive
< critical is always true (unless there is an underflow).

Hence remove this check

This is fix for issue #407

build warning, ret is assigned for sysfs write

Fix warning:
CXX src/thermald-thd_cdev_gen_sysfs.o
src/thd_cdev_gen_sysfs.cpp:42:3: warning: Value stored to 'ret' is never read [deadcode.DeadStores]
ret = cdev_sysfs.write("", 0);

Here return THD_ERROR if ret < 0.

Fix for issue #405.

Remove duplicate type_type == HOT comparison

Instead of two trip_type comparisons with HOT, one should be TRIP_CRITICAL.

Fix for issue #404

Remove unused variables sysfs and buffer

The variables are declared and never referenced, they are redundant
and can be removed.

Signed-off-by: Colin Ian King <colin.i.king@gmail.com>

Remove redundant inverted logic check on offset

The check for offset >= len seems to be redundant, it is used
on a while-loop where the only way we can reach the if statement
is when offset < len, in which case the offset >= len check is
never true. Remove it. Cleans up cppcheck warning:

src/thd_gddv.cpp:209:14: warning: Opposite inner 'if' condition leads to a dead code block. [oppositeInnerCondition]
  if (offset >= len)
             ^
src/thd_gddv.cpp:206:16: note: outer condition: offset<len
 while (offset < len) {
               ^
src/thd_gddv.cpp:209:14: note: opposite inner condition: offset>=len
  if (offset >= len)
             ^
Signed-off-by: Colin Ian King <colin.i.king@gmail.com>

Remove unused variable sys_fs

The variable is declared and never referenced, it is redundant and can
be removed.

Signed-off-by: Colin Ian King <colin.i.king@gmail.com>

Remove some unused string declarations

Minor code cleanup, remove tc_state_dev, state_str and temp_str as
they are unused, as found by cppcheck:

src/thd_cdev_rapl.cpp:34:20: style: Unused variable: tc_state_dev [unusedVariable]
 std::stringstream tc_state_dev;
                   ^
src/thd_cdev_rapl.cpp:36:20: style: Unused variable: state_str [unusedVariable]
 std::stringstream state_str;
                   ^
src/thd_cdev_rapl.cpp:367:20: style: Unused variable: temp_str [unusedVariable]
 std::stringstream temp_str;
                   ^
Signed-off-by: Colin Ian King <colin.i.king@gmail.com>

Remove duplicated assignment to pl0_min_window

pl0_min_window is being assigned the same value twice, remove the duplicate

Signed-off-by: Colin Ian King <colin.i.king@gmail.com>

Fix powerclamp test

Kernel driver changed min state to 0. This require change in the
test script.

Fix test scripts

Warn about running thermald with --adaptive option.
Also fix powerclamp max state to 49. The kernel default
max is always 100.

Fix test module

There is change in the kernel, so update the test module.
Assign the max_state before calling cooling device register.

Merge pull request #403 from intel/2.5.4_merge_branch

2.5.4 merge branch

Merge pull request #398 from pabs3/qcustomplot-library-change

Update the QCustomPlot library name

Merge pull request #397 from pabs3/cleanup

Clean up typos, grammar, shebangs, regex, commands, links, paths, manual pages

Merge pull request #396 from pabs3/configurable-power-group

Make the dbus power group configurable

2.5.4 pre release

This address issue with some Lenovo T14s, where none of adaptive
conditions match, here install the default passive table.

Support reading of passive tables

Read via IOCTL the passive table entries, if present. This
helps older systems which don't have adaptive tables.

Porting adative policy support for Android

Following items are done for Android:
   Porting lzma functions from intel dptf project
   Remove UpClient
   Remove libevdev-devel related code in android
   Add adaptive related handle in android_main.c
   Fix android.mk

Install passive when target fails to match

It is possible that some OEM variable conditions are present, this
is a special case as this will always match during init. So there
will not be any fallback even if later none of the conditions
with OEM variable match.

In this case during periodic call to update_engine_state() install
IETM D0 default entry.

Workaround for missing PSVT or ITMT target

When there is no PSVT or ITMT target is specified, currently it
fallbacks to the sysfs defaults for CPU thermal zone. It is possible
that those CPU sysfs entries are never validated by the OEM.

So fallback to IETM_D0 table if present. Since this table is in the
GDDV, hopefully this is correct.

configure.ac: Install dbus policy in /usr/share, not /etc

From https://bugs.debian.org/1006631:

> dbus supports policy files in both `/usr/share/dbus-1/system.d` and
> `/etc/dbus-1/systemd`. [The] recently released dbus 1.14.0, officially
> deprecates installing packages' default policies into `/etc/dbus-1/systemd`,
> instead reserving it for the sysadmin. This is the same idea as the
> difference between `/usr/lib/udev/rules.d` and `/etc/udev/rules.d`.

Release 2.5.3

Refer to README.txt for changes

Add support for Mateor Lake

Add support for Matero Lake by adding CPU model and sysfs paths.

Update the QCustomPlot library name

The library name was changed to title case in QCustomPlot 2.1.0.

Make the dbus power group configurable

This means that distros can choose their pre-existing power management group
or just choose a less generic group than 'power' such as '_thermald-managers'.

Closes: https://github.com/intel/thermal_daemon/issues/162
See-also: https://bugs.debian.org/864502

Drop empty/skipped .TP and .PP in manual pages

Suggested-by: mandoc

Fix dates in manual pages

Suggested-by: mandoc

Update links for https, redirects, moved repos and archived pages

Suggested-by: check-all-the-things

Drop mention of where qmake is installed

It is more likely to be installed from distro packages than /opt
and the person who installed qmake would know where they put it.

Suggested-by: check-all-the-things

Switch from apt-get to apt for installing Ubuntu dependencies

The apt-get tool is for non-interactive usage and apt for interactive use.

Fix regex for finding the current branch

Escape the asterisk character.

Suggested-by: shellcheck
See-also: https://www.shellcheck.net/wiki/SC2063

Fix shell script header shebangs

Suggested-by: shellcheck
See-also: https://www.shellcheck.net/wiki/SC1104

Fix typos and grammar

Suggested-by: anorack, codespell, spellintian & proselint
Merge branch 'master' of https://github.com/intel/thermal_daemon

Fix example for RAPL power limits

The max and min PPCC limits are swapped. Fix that.

Add RAPL power limit example

Update the thermal-conf.xml man page using RAPL power limits.

development_2.5.3.commit_message:
Workaround for missing PSVT or ITMT target

When there is no PSVT or ITMT target is specified, currently it
fallbacks to the sysfs defaults for CPU thermal zone. It is possible
that those CPU sysfs entries are never validated by the OEM.

So fallback to IETM_D0 table if present. Since this table is in the
GDDV, hopefully this is correct.

Also when none of the conditions match install IETM_D0.

Support reading of passive tables

Read via IOCTL the passive table entries, if present. This
helps older systems which don't have adaptive tables.

configure.ac: Install dbus policy in /usr/share, not /etc

From https://bugs.debian.org/1006631:

> dbus supports policy files in both `/usr/share/dbus-1/system.d` and
> `/etc/dbus-1/systemd`. [The] recently released dbus 1.14.0, officially
> deprecates installing packages' default policies into `/etc/dbus-1/systemd`,
> instead reserving it for the sysadmin. This is the same idea as the
> difference between `/usr/lib/udev/rules.d` and `/etc/udev/rules.d`.

Porting adative policy support for Android

Following items are done for Android:
   Porting lzma functions from intel dptf project
   Remove UpClient
   Remove libevdev-devel related code in android
   Add adaptive related handle in android_main.c
   Fix android.mk

Release 2.5.3

Refer to README.txt for changes

Add support for Mateor Lake

Add support for Matero Lake by adding CPU model and sysfs paths.

Fix example for RAPL power limits

The max and min PPCC limits are swapped. Fix that.

Add RAPL power limit example

Update the thermal-conf.xml man page using RAPL power limits.
